It was confirmed that the 27-year-old, who is still on trial for murder, needed to sell the property to raise money for his legal bills, which total up to £5,000 per day.

According to the Times Live in South Africa, the buyer Louwtjie Louwrens, plans to retire to the property with his family.

He told the newspaper: 'It is in a safe area and everyone I dealt with was very professional.

'It stood empty for more than a year and there is some water damage, so we would first have to repair it.'

Since the shooting in the early hours of Valentine's Day last year, Pistorius has been living at his uncle's house in Pretoria.

