The costs - reportedly as high as £5,000 ($9,000) a day - are said to include at least three full-time lawyers in court, ballistics and forensics experts as well as an American crime scene reconstruction company.

Pistorius is charged with premeditated murder and faces 25 years to life in prison if convicted.

He says he shot Miss Steenkamp, 29, by mistake through a locked door in his bathroom because he thought she was a dangerous night time intruder.

